theme_override_font_sizes/font_size = 28
text = "Goal: Form a five-in-a-row in any direction before your opponent does.

Playing: Each turn consists of placing one marble on any empty space on the board, then twisting any of the blocks 90 degrees in either direction.

Game End: When a five-in-a-row is formed, the game ends and the player who owns the five-in-a-row wins! If a five-in-a-row is made for both players simultaneously, or if all spaces are filled and there are no five-in-a-rows after the rotation phase, then it is a tie.

Pentago XL: This is a larger variant has a bigger grid and supports team play. Teams can own 1 or 2 colors, but must still make a five-in-a-row out of one of their owned colors (making a Blue+Red five-in-a-row is not possible)."
autowrap_mode = 3

